translated: Johannesson, Bror Fritiof, city official, Jönköping, born on April 8th, 1907 in Hälsingborg, to parents August J. and Karin Petersson. Married in 1938 to Märta Berglund. Children: Sune, born in 1941. Graduated from high school in Hälsingborg in 1926, received a law degree from Lund University in 1931. Served as a court clerk in N. Asbo District Court from 1932 to 1934, worked at the Skåne and Blekinge Court of Appeal in 1935 and 1937, acted as a temporary mayor and public notary in Ronneby in 1936 and from 1938 to 1943, served as a city mayor and public notary there from 1944 to 1947, and has been a city official in Jönköping since 1947.
